{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"87be75f0-fb6f-4166-802c-b765b69b6814","content":"In .NET MAUI, you use **lifecycle event mappings** in `MauiProgram.cs` via `ConfigureLifecycleEvents`:\n\n```csharp\nusing Microsoft.Maui.LifecycleEvents;\n\nbuilder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>\n{\n#if ANDROID\n    events.AddAndroid(android => android\n        .OnPause(activity =>\n        {\n            // Runs when the activity is pausing\n        })\n        .OnStop(activity =>\n        {\n            // Runs when the activity is no longer visible\n        }));\n#endif\n\n#if IOS\n    events.AddiOS(ios => ios\n        .DidEnterBackground(app =>\n        {\n            // Runs when the app enters the background\n        }));\n#endif\n});\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- Add the `Microsoft.Maui.LifecycleEvents` namespace.\n- Use **platform compiler directives** (`#if ANDROID`, `#if IOS`) to keep platform code separated.\n- Each platform exposes its native events: `OnPause`, `OnStop`, `OnResume`, etc. for Android; `DidEnterBackground`, `WillEnterForeground`, etc. for iOS.\n- This all lives in your `MauiProgram.CreateMauiApp()` builder pipeline — no custom platform code files needed.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"0f6bdaf4-72a2-4151-8b92-53fbffc9b3fd","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to hook into platform-specific lifecycle events in .NET MAUI — specifically Android's OnPause/OnStop and iOS's DidEnterBackground. This is a general knowledge question about .NET MAUI, not a codebase-specific task. I can answer this directly.","outputTokens":410,"requestId":"77E8:28BCD7:7F61607:8D92EA2:69EABE39"},"id":"2bfd50ed-4ac7-4615-aa8d-3c4f387d78cb","timestamp":"2026-04-24T00:50:10.327Z","parentId":"fbc8ce62-c566-403c-ab79-30a29f9d209d"}
